Three Kenya Police Reservists were shot dead at Kalua in Igembe Central by suspected Turkana bandits. Four others sustained bullet injuries. The attack happened on Wednesday during an evening ambush. OCPD confirmed that the attack took place along the border between Igembe Central and Isiolo North.  "It is alleged Turkana criminals invaded and suddenly attacked and a shootout broke. We have lost three of our KPR officers. We are following up the criminals," Rashid said. Click here for the latest political news 